HEADWORD: Culmen
<hw>Cul"men</hw> <pr>(k?l"m?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>cellere</ets> (in comp.) to impel; cf. <ets>celsus</ets> pushed
upward, lofty.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Top; summit; acme.</def>
<rj><au>R. North.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The dorsal ridge of a bird's
bill.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Culmiferous</ent>⟦br⟧
